    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Looks like this needs to be solved on a protocol level. /cc'ing @cammellos \r\nWhether or not a transaction is considered a \"request\" depends on its `commandState`. When a transaction is declined, it changes its state so we no longer know whether it originates from a request or not.\r\n\r\n@cammellos do you think we could put that information into tx data coming from status?",
